insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-0756404741', 1, 'I read this book with conflicting sentiments and reactions. It has been compared with The Glass Castle, a memoir which I loved.', '2019-06-12', 5, 1);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-0756404741', 5, 'I admit I felt some degree of skepticism. There seemed to be contradictions and gaps which needed further explanation. At times I felt it was documenting a nasty family feud while her recollection of family dynamics and its surrounding radical religious fanaticism and paranoia altered in her thinking.', '2019-06-06', 5, 0);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-0756404741', 6, 'Excellent memoir. Beautifully and powerfully written.', '2019-04-26', 2, 1);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-1627792127', 9, 'This is a powerful story of several strains of conflict within the human condition and how one remarkable individual liberated herself from the destructive forces of a dysfunctional family and the the madness within it.', '2019-08-13', 5, 0);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-1627792127', 10, 'Excellent memoir and the best I’ve ever read. Westover is careful to be as “objective” as one can be when writing about oneself. What is so amazing is how each child in the family turns out differently despite being raised in the same damaging atmosphere by off-the- grid parents.', '2019-06-11', 3, 1);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-1627792127', 2, 'A very well written account of how one needs to determine their own reality rather than have it defined by the circumstances in which they were raised. Overcoming almost unimaginable odds, the author obtained a university degree, a masters degree, and then a PhD. ', '2019-09-07', 5, 1);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-1627792127', 3, 'This was a truly great read. I could not put it down. At first, it reminded me of another book I d read recently, but pretty soon it developed it is own twisted relationships and I was hooked! The ending was a complete surprise. Loved it!', '2019-04-14', 4, 1);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-1627792127', 4, 'Loved the book, well written with many surprises in the narrative and well-drawn characters. Could not wait to see who was guilty but hated having reached the end of the story. I recommended it to my book club.', '2020-02-02', 4, 0);
insert into Review (ISBN, AccountID , ReviewText , PostDate , Rating , Approval) values ('978-0439023498', 7, 'Love these novels that take you for a good ride until the end result. Very enjoyable read.', '2020-01-05', 5, 1);
